The '''Master Instructor''' was the title bestowed to the head of the [[Imperial Royal Guard Academy]]. The title was first given to [[Ved Kennede]], one of [[Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine's]] first guardsmen. Due to his loyalty and exemplary service, Palpatine put him in charge of the [[Imperial Royal Guard Academy]] with Kennede as its head. This prestigious title gave Kennede the responsibility of training and choosing the future generation of guardsmen. Along with this title came a special suit of armor which was similar to regular guardsmen armor except for a distinct painting of black which covered select portions of the helmet and the breastplate, similar to the [[Imperial Sovereign Protector]]s.

After Kennede's death in an [[Attack on the Imperial Royal Guard Academy]], the armor was usurped by guardsmen traitor, [[Carnor Jax]] who wore the armor everywhere after assuming the position of [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Galactic Emperor]]. However, after Jax was killed in a [[Duel in The Squall]], by [[Kir Kanos]], the helmet was thrown into the depths of [[The Squall/Legends|the Squall]]. A similar suit of armor was eventually worn by [[Chik Apla]], one of the members of the rejuvenated guard under [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Natasi Daala]]. The Master instructor oversaw all guard regiments.

